2.10	Zavidovo	Zavidovo	Zavidovo in Konakovsky District of Tver Oblast, Russia. It is used as an official residence place for the President of Russia, and was also used by the Soviet leaders. The residence is situated in the Zavidovo nature reserve. According to UNESCO, Zavidovo is one of the most environmentally safe places on the planet. The nature reserve is situated 150 kilometres away from Moscow in both Moscow and Tver Oblasts, on the banks of the Shosha River (a tributary of the Volga) and Lama River, and on the shore of the Ivankovo Reservoir.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8c/Zavidovo.JPG/220px-Zavidovo.JPG
